{"questionId":"22661960","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Now consider points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> close to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> on the phase plane. These coordinates can be rewritten as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math> are the values from part (b)(ii).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>foxes.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mn>5</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mn>5</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>5</mn></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>&nbsp;(hundred foxes per year) / <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1000</mn></math> (foxes per year)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22661960","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.2aii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"foxes.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
